<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1324,284,1510]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,646,1164,1190]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Geographical distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smetana" authorityYear="2005" box="[656,904,1164,1189]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Sphaerobulbus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusio">
<emphasis box="[656,904,1164,1189]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Sphaerobulbus pusio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<materialsCitation location="Daliang Shan" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Sichuan">
is at present known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[264,314,1204,1230]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">type</typeStatus>
locality in 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03C0BB41FFC2304BC769FCA3780605ED:8EB65C8CFFC1304BC7DEFB63793804C5" box="[447,606,1204,1230]" name="Daliang Shan" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" stateProvince="Sichuan">Daliang Shan</location>
in southern 
<collectingRegion box="[752,850,1204,1230]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1324,284,1510]" box="[312,1199,1244,1270]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,449,1244,1270]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Bionomics.</emphasis>
Nothing is known about the habitat requirement of this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1324,284,1510]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,469,1284,1310]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Recognition.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smetana" authorityYear="2005" box="[481,732,1284,1309]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Sphaerobulbus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusio">
<emphasis box="[481,732,1284,1309]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Sphaerobulbus pusio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is at present the by far smallest species of the genus; it cannot be confused with any other species. It is obviously a member of the “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smetana" authorityYear="2003" box="[277,397,1364,1389]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Sphaerobulbus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bisinuatus">
<emphasis box="[277,397,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">bisinuatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
­group” of the genus (see Smetana 2003: 69), although the configuration of the basal portions of the first three visible abdominal tergites is not fully developed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1324,284,1510]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,452,1444,1470]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is the Latin noun 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smetana" authorityYear="2005" box="[935,998,1444,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Sphaerobulbus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusio">
<emphasis box="[935,998,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">pusio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, ­ 
<emphasis box="[1027,1076,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">onis</emphasis>
, m. (a little boy) in apposition. It refers to the small size of the species.
</paragraph>
